WHY BRANDFOLDER?

BRANDFOLDER CHECKS ALL THE BOXES

  • business model = subscription
  • technology = SaaS
  • total addressable market = anyone with a brand
  • provides distinct solution to meaningful problem
    • they come for asset management; they stay for the analytics
  • strong growth with very little churn

MARKETING

PERSON SCORING

  • in Salesforce, Leads & Contacts are people
    • Leads are people you probably want to know
    • Contacts are people you actually know
  • who are these people? what is their role?
  • what have they done? what have they responded to?

ACCOUNT SCORING

  • combine people scores with account attributes
  • can grade accounts by industry, size, technology, age
    • grouped into A, B, and C grades below

WHICH EVENTS TO INVEST IN?

  • each event requires an investment
  • each event should yield a return
    • brand awareness
    • lead acquisition
    • nurture

EVALUATING EVENTS

OPTIMIZING MARKETING INVESTMENTS

  • mind the lag
    • todays investments may not yield bookings for months, years
  • decide if OpportunityContactRole is important or not
    • this decision and data drives attribution
  • milestones to measure
    • how did we acquire the person record?
    • what was first thing they responded to?
    • what did they respond to before the deal created?
    • what did they respond to after deal created but before won?

INTERPRETTING THE JOURNEY REQUIRES ROBUST PROCESSES

  • what if only Hans appeared in OpportunityContactRole?
  • what if John was organic but Has result of paid media?

ACCOUNT FAMILIES REQUIRE DECISIONS

  • this is where things often go wrong
  • what are rules of engagement?
    • does ownership happen at family (parent)? each node?

LAND, RETAIN, AND EXPAND

  • requires a flywheel data set of subscription line items
    • account, product, arr, start date, end date
  • find attributes associated with churn risk: size? industry? usage?
  • timing and kind of expansion: adding seats or products?
